Package MainGameLogic

Class SetUp

java.lang.Object
MainGameLogic.SetUp
public final class SetUp
extends java.lang.Object
This class implements a "static" class SetUp which hold the initialized information for the MainGameLogic.GameEnvironment and can we accessed but not initialized itself.
Version:
1.1, 16 April 2021.
Author:
John Elliott

    • initializeIslands

      public static java.util.ArrayList<Island> initializeIslands()
      Uses default values and information to initialize all the Islands. Adds each new MainGameLogic.Island to the islands ArrayList.

      islands A list of all default islands.

    • initializeStores

      public static void initializeStores​(java.util.ArrayList<Island> islands)
      Makes a Store for each MainGameLogic.Island within the islands list. These Store are per-determined.
      Parameters:
      islands - A list of Islands currently in the MainGameLogic.GameEnvironment.

    • initializeShip

      Returns:
